<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="25Apr1933"><font color="red">25 April 1933</font> <i>Letters III</i> (to Harriet Weaver from Paul L&eacute;on): On Friday night (21 April 1933) Mr Joyce suffered from a very bad attack of colitis &hellip; If I were to describe his state today I would call it that of a listless disgust and apathy in connection with the most vital problems of his life and work. The latter is not even considered today and whenever I mention the subject Mr Joyce merely waves his hand in despair and resignation &hellip; He has arranged to stay in the flat until the 15th of May &hellip; His usual remark is &lsquo;let everything go to pieces&rsquo; </div>
